{{Quote|<nowiki />''Star Wars'' is the love story of my life.|Jerome Blake|<ref name="200 Reasons Why We Love Star Wars">{{InsiderCite|200|200 Reasons Why We Love Star Wars|200 Reasons Why We Love ''Star Wars''}}</ref>}}
'''Jerome Blake''' played [[Mas Amedda]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']]. He also played [[Oppo Rancisis]] in ''Episode I'' and ''II'', and [[Rune Haako]], [[Mik Regrap]], [[Horox Ryyder]], [[Graxol Kelvyyn]], and [[Orn Free Taa]] in ''Episode I''. He also filmed scenes for [[Solo: A Star Wars Story]] that were deleted from the final film where he played a new character known as The Mad Uncle.<ref>{{YouTube|video=JI0Z5gDusuI|text=LIVE at Soho Theatre in London with Pierre Bohanna & Jerome Blake|channel=@TheGeorgeLucasTalkShow|name=The George Lucas Talk Show|date=2023-05-27|archivedate=20230607135001}}</ref>

He has played minor roles in many different films and commercials. He is usually under a mask or being the voice of a character, and is therefore rarely recognized in public. For many years he was musician and at age 36 became a model.

